[0.001, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2B\u001b[56A\r\u001b[J\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 2. Check the mcp-servers to see what servers are available\u001b[39m\r\n\r\u001b[J\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 3. Check the llm package features to understand what providers are supported\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\u001b[38;2;194;217;76mвң“\u001b[39m Read file\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m (Cargo.toml, 50 lines)\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;194;217;76mвң“\u001b[39m Run command\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m (ls -la /Users/josh/code/aether/packag... (exit 0))\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;194;217;76mвң“\u001b[39m Run command\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m (ls /Users/josh/code/aether/packages/m... (exit 0))\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ I see that there's no separate `bin` directory for aether-acp. Let me check what binaries are actually av\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mailable in aether-cli and also check the main.rs to see what commands are available.\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\u001b[38;2;194;217;76mвң“\u001b[39m Read file\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m (main.rs, 60 lines +rules: writing-rust)\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;194;217;76mвң“\u001b[39m Read file\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m (Cargo.toml, 103 lines)\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ Now I have a better understanding of the current stat"]
[0.000, "o", "e:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 1. **Providers**: The README lists: \"OpenAI, OpenRouter, Google, DeepSeek, Moonshot, Zai, Llama.cpp, and \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mOllama\" but looking at the providers directory, I see:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - anthropic\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - bedrock (AWS Bedrock)\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - codex\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - deepseek\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - gemini\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - local (likely for Ollama/Llama.cpp)\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - moonshot\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - openai\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - openai_compatible\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - openrouter\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - z_ai\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 2. **MCP servers**: The README lists: coding, skills, tasks, subagents, survey - which matches the mcp-se\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mrvers directory. There's also a `proxy` server now based on the mcp.json.\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m"]
[0.000, "o", "в”Ӯ 3. **Binaries**: The README mentions `aether-acp` as a separate binary, but now it's a subcommand `aether\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m acp`. Also `aether headless` instead of running the binary with arguments.\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 4. **Packages**: There are new packages not mentioned:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - aether-project\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - crucible\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - aether-lspd\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - acp-utils\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - mcp-utils\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - utils\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - tui\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 5. **The CLI commands have changed**:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - Old: `cargo run -p aether-cli --bin aether -- -m anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-20250514 \"Refactor auth m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92module\"`\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - New: Should be `cargo run -p aether-cli --bin aether -- headless -m anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-202505\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m14 \"Refactor auth "]
[0.000, "o", "module\"`\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - Old: `cargo run -p aether-cli --bin aether-acp -- --model anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-20250514 --mcp-c\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92monfig mcp.json`\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ   \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;255;180;84mвЈҜ\u001b[38;2;144;143;134m Tip: Hit Shift+Tab to cycle through agent modes\u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m  (esc to interrupt)\u001b[0m\u001b[39m\u001b[49m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв•ӯв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв•®\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;230;225;207m> \u001b[39m                                                                                                      \u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв•°в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ"]
