[0.000, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2B\u001b[56A\r\u001b[J\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ Now I have a better understanding of the current state:\u001b[39m\r\n\r\u001b[J\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 1. **Providers**: The README lists: \"OpenAI, OpenRouter, Google, DeepSeek, Moonshot, Zai, Llama.cpp, and \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mOllama\" but looking at the providers directory, I see:\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - anthropic\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - bedrock (AWS Bedrock)\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - codex\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - deepseek\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - gemini\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - local (likely for Ollama/Llama.cpp)\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - moonshot\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - openai\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - openai_compatible\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - openrouter\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ    - z_ai\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 2. **MCP servers**: The README lists: coding, skills, tasks, subagents, survey - which matches the mcp-se\u001b[39m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mrvers directory. There's also a `proxy` server now based on the mcp.json.\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ 3. **Binaries**: The README mentions `aether-acp` as a separate binary, but now it's a subcommand `aether\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;69;80;92m acp`. Also `aether headless` instead of running the binary with arguments.\u001b[39m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[38;2;69;80;92mв”Ӯ \u001b[39m\r\n"]
